parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts down without warning
the engine takes a long time to restart (up to 15 minutes)
the problem is more frequent in wet or damp weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft can cause the engine to seize, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle loses power and stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the K-frame can cause the vehicle to lose structural integrity, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to come to a sudden halt
and potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear gate support can cause the gate to fall down, potentially striking the consumer on the head or causing injuries, and making it difficult to load or unload items.
symptoms: The rear gate falls down when trying to open or close it
making it difficult to load or unload items

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear box mounting can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering gear box is noisy
the steering gear box is leaking fluid
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle pulls to one side.
